package app

// PostBuild is the user-owned two-phase wiring hook (FORGE_SHAPE_REDESIGN
// §2). It runs AFTER Build (internal/app/inject_gen.go) has constructed the
// whole component graph and BEFORE the server begins serving. Its job is
// the wiring the type-topological injector cannot express:
//
//   - two-phase setters / post-construction injection, e.g.
//       s.Billing.WithReliantAPIKeyIssuer(s.LLM)
//   - breaking a dependency cycle the injector flagged (the back-edge is
//     left nil by Build; complete it here once both endpoints exist).
//
// Lifecycle:
//
//  1. OpenInfra builds the owned *Infra (providers.go).
//  2. Build constructs every component in type-topological order,
//     returning *Services.
//  3. PostBuild (THIS function) runs the two-phase setters. An error here
//     aborts the server boot.
//  4. The cmd layer selects which Mount funcs to call and serves.
//
// Why this hook exists (vs. doing it in OpenInfra): the setters here need
// CONSTRUCTED components (s.Billing, s.LLM), which only exist after Build —
// step 2. A constructor-order injector cannot wire them.
//
// Default body is a no-op; the user owns the file after first emit and
// forge generate will not overwrite it.
//
// yours: scaffolded once, never touched again — forge will not overwrite this file
//
//forge:allow
func PostBuild(s *Services) error {
	_ = s
	return nil
}
